Thus was actually my first time at Qdoba.  One of the few places in the loop open the day after Thanksgiving. Thank you to the workers for being there, being pleasant, and feeding me.  The food was very good and prices reasonable for the loop. I had the 3 taco meal and tried the pork, chicken, and vegetarian. All were very good. My wife had the nachos. They too were very good and the queso was pleasantly more spicy than expected. She had it with pastor. Highly recommended.  They have the now almost standard Coke product 1,000 options machine. I appreciate the zero sugar fruit flavor options to add to zero sugar sodas.  Bonus points for keeping cholula original and Tabasco Jalapeno green hot sauces available. Also there are 2 pokestops you can reach from here provided you don't sift too much.
